import java.io.File;
import java.io.FileOutputStream;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.net.URI;
import java.nio.file.Files;
import java.nio.file.Path;
import java.nio.file.StandardCopyOption;
import java.util.Base64;



public interface FileParser {
    void parseCSV(File csvFile);
    File convertCSVDataToImage(String base64ImageData);
    URI createImageLink(File fileImage);
}

public class ImageFileParser implements FileParser {
    private static final String IMAGES_DIRECTORY = "images/";

    @Override
    public void parseCSV(File csvFile) {
        // Implement the parsing logic to read the CSV file and store the records into a database
        // You can use libraries like OpenCSV or Apache Commons CSV to parse the CSV file
    }

    @Override
    public File convertCSVDataToImage(String base64ImageData) {
        try {
            byte[] imageBytes = Base64.getDecoder().decode(base64ImageData);

            File imageFile = File.createTempFile("image_", ".jpg");
            try (FileOutputStream fos = new FileOutputStream(imageFile)) {
                fos.write(imageBytes);
            }

            return imageFile;
        } catch (IOException e) {
            // Handle exception appropriately
            e.printStackTrace();
            return null;
        }
    }

    @Override
    public URI createImageLink(File fileImage) {
        try {
            Path imagePath = Path.of(IMAGES_DIRECTORY, fileImage.getName());
            Files.move(fileImage.toPath(), imagePath, StandardCopyOption.REPLACE_EXISTING);
            return imagePath.toUri();
        } catch (IOException e) {
            // Handle exception appropriately
            e.printStackTrace();
            return null;
        }
    }
}

import org.springframework.core.io.FileSystemResource;

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/v1/api/image")
@RequestMapping("/v2/api/image")
public class ImageController {
